(548, '<ul><li>TheCollectivwasborninthesummerof2001inOakland,CA.OurorganizationwasfoundedbyA.Williams,akaSokrates,withamissionto"empowertheHipHopcommunitythrougheducationandentrepreneurship."Wepursuethismissionbysponsoringadiverserangeofprogramswithdistinctyetcooperativegoals.Weworkwithyoungentrepreneurs,activistsandartiststodesignfinanciallyviableprogramsthatwillprovidenewopportunitiesforempowerment.Weseektocreatetheperfectenvironmentforturninganideaintoimpact.<li>TheCollectivcurrentlysponsorsthreeprograms,CollectivRecords,CollectivArts&EntertainmentandCollectivFoundation.EachoftheseprogramsoccupiesadistinctnichewithintheHipHopcommunity.</li></ul>', 'ugc', 'D:\\DATA\\tmm\\tmtweb\\application\\views\\projects_table.php', 69, '/team?qtfilter=Jamie%20Williams', 'localhost.taylormadetraffic.com', NULL, '<ul>\n                <li>The Collectiv was born in the summer of 2001 in Oakland, CA. Our organization was founded by A. Williams, aka Sokrates, with a mission to "empower the Hip Hop community through education and entrepreneurship." We pursue this mission by sponsoring a diverse range of programs with distinct yet cooperative goals. We work with young entrepreneurs, activists and artists to design financially viable programs that will provide new opportunities for empowerment. We seek to create the perfect environment for turning an idea into impact.\n                <li>The Collectiv currently sponsors three programs, Collectiv Records, Collectiv Arts & Entertainment and Collectiv Foundation. Each of these programs occupies a distinct niche within the Hip Hop community.</li>\n                </ul>', 'en', 'debug', 1389136609, '2014-01-07 23:16:49'),
(549, 'IDinteractivebuildsmarketingplatformsforalonglistofgreatclientswithcreativeprojectsandcampaigns.OneofthemostfunIbuiltinaquick4weekswas.Thecampaignwasbasedon20millioncodesprintedonOreopackagesthroughoutColombia.Therewere5typesofprizestowininvaryingamountswithatotalof285togive.Noonecodecouldbeconsideredawinnerinadvance,andtheprizesshouldbedistributedevenlythroughoutthe~60daycampaign.Iwrotetheprobabilitytoberelatedtotheaveragenumberofpeopleplayingdailyanddistributedallprizes-bynumberandtype–evenlyuntilthelastday.', 'ugc', 'D:\\DATA\\tmm\\tmtweb\\application\\views\\projects_table.php', 69, '/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor', 'localhost.taylormadetraffic.com', NULL, 'IDinteractive builds marketing platforms for a long list of great clients with creative projects and campaigns. One of the most fun I built in a quick 4 weeks was . The campaign was based on 20 million codes printed on Oreo packages throughout Colombia. There were 5 types of prizes to win in varying amounts with a total of 285 to give.  No one code could be considered a winner in advance, and the prizes should be distributed evenly throughout the ~60 day campaign. I wrote the probability to be related to the average number of people playing daily and distributed all prizes - by number and type – evenly until the last day.', 'en', 'debug', 1389136657, '2014-01-07 23:17:37'),
(550, 'Asearchagainstthe20millioncodestook.00020seconds,andthesitesupportedbusinessrulessuchasCatpchawhenausersearchedmorethan12timesinaday.IalsoincludedseveralbackendtrackingtoolsandaautomatedQAtestertosimulatevaryingdegreesoftraffic,codesearches,andminimumprobabilities.', 'ugc', 'D:\\DATA\\tmm\\tmtweb\\application\\views\\projects_table.php', 70, '/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor', 'localhost.taylormadetraffic.com', NULL, 'A search against the 20 million codes took .00020 seconds, and the site supported business rules such as Catpcha when a user searched more than 12 times in a day. I also included several backend tracking tools and a automated QA tester to simulate varying degrees of traffic, code searches, and minimum probabilities.', 'en', 'debug', 1389136657, '2014-01-07 23:17:37'),
