(560, 'Thewebsite''srunsinaLAMPenvironment,andishighlyoptimizedbyseveralBashscripts.OneisrunfromaCRONtouseImageMagickforcroppingandresizingimagesbasedonautomatedcuetablemaintainedwhenasizeorshapeisrequestedthathasnotyetbeencut.Anotherisforre-indexingthemusiccatalogue-of20,000songsandgrowing.ItextendsatoolcalledBeetstocorrectmp3meta-data,downloadartworkandlyrics,anddeterminesound-waveaveragessuchasBPM(beats-per-minute)andReplayGain(usedtodetermineaverageencodeddecibelvolumeofthesoundwave).ThebackendsystemalsoincludesanasynchronousemailservicewhichIlinkedseamlesslytothefront-endwebpagetemplateswithaCSSinlinerscript.Thesitescalesverywelltoallscreenwidthsabove320pixelswide,butIamwellunderwaywithanativeAndroidversionoftheplayerwith0-100scalemusicratingstorefinetherotationofsongs.', 'ugc', 'D:\\DATA\\tmm\\tmtweb\\application\\views\\projects_table.php', 70, '/team?qtfilter=E.A.Taylor', 'localhost.taylormadetraffic.com', NULL, 'The website''s runs in a LAMP environment, and is highly optimized by several Bash scripts. One is run from a CRON to use ImageMagick for cropping and resizing images based on automated cue table maintained when a size or shape is requested that has not yet been cut.  Another is for re-indexing the music catalogue - of 20,000 songs and growing. It extends a tool called Beets to correct mp3 meta-data, download artwork and lyrics, and determine sound-wave averages such as BPM (beats-per-minute) and Replay Gain (used to determine average encoded decibel volume of the sound wave). The backend system also includes an asynchronous email service which I linked seamlessly to the front-end webpage templates with a CSS inliner script. The site scales very well to all screen widths above 320 pixels wide, but I am well underway with a native Android version of the player with 0-100 scale music ratings to refine the rotation of songs.', 'en', 'debug', 1389136657, '2014-01-07 23:17:37'),
