(662, 'ThewebsiterunsinaLAMPenvironment,andishighlyoptimizedbyseveralBashscripts<ul><li>OneisrunfromaCRONtouseImageMagickforcroppingandresizingimagesbasedonautomatedcuetablemaintainedwhenasizeorshapeisrequestedthathasnotyetbeencut.</li><li>Anotherisforre-indexingthemusiccatalogue-of20,000songsandgrowing.ItextendsatoolcalledBeetstocorrectmp3meta-data,downloadartworkandlyrics,anddeterminesound-waveaveragessuchasBPM(beats-per-minute)andReplayGain(usedtodetermineaverageencodeddecibelvolumeofthesoundwave).</li><li>ThebackendsystemalsoincludesanasynchronousemailservicewhichIlinkedseamlesslytothefront-endwebpagetemplateswithaCSSinlinerscript.</li><li>Thesitescalesverywelltoallscreenwidthsabove320pixelswide,butIamwellunderwaywithanativeAndroidversionoftheplayerwith0-100scalemusicratingstorefinetherotationofsongs.</li><li>ItalsoincludesaCodeIgniterpluginthatmanagestranslationsofsystemcopyanduser-generatedcontent,withversioncontrollingtextchangesbyauthorizeduser/authors.</li></ul>', 'ugc', 'D:\\DATA\\tmm\\tmtweb\\application\\views\\projects_table.php', 70, '/eli', 'localhost.taylormadetraffic.com', NULL, 'The website runs in a LAMP environment, and is highly optimized by several Bash scripts\n                    <ul>\n                    <li>One is run from a CRON to use ImageMagick for cropping and resizing images based on automated cue table maintained when a size or shape is requested that has not yet been cut.</li>\n                    <li>Another is for re-indexing the music catalogue - of 20,000 songs and growing. It extends a tool called Beets to correct mp3 meta-data, download artwork and lyrics, and determine sound-wave averages such as BPM (beats-per-minute) and Replay Gain (used to determine average encoded decibel volume of the sound wave).</li>\n                    <li>The backend system also includes an asynchronous email service which I linked seamlessly to the front-end webpage templates with a CSS inliner script.</li>\n                    <li>The site scales